<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="100" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,582,607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In female, tubiform structures of sperm induction system relatively large, with apices adjacent but separated, moderately narrowed toward apices, vase-like (
<figureCitation box="[852,947,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Figs 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[968,1042,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 26" captionStartId="8.[151,263,977,1000]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,957]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,957]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 26. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov., sperm induction structures, female, variant forms. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322032/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">23‒26</figureCitation>
). Male spermatodactyl expanded submedially, leaf-like, without distinct angustate subdistal or apical portion, less than double the length of the movable digit (
<figureCitation box="[334,427,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Figs 20</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[446,478,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 56" captionStartId="19.[151,263,1900,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,195,1879]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 56. Chelicerae, males, with variant forms of spermatodactyls. 53. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) abludens sp. nov.; 54. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov.; 55. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) pantinii sp. nov.; 56. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) marcovallei sp. nov. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322039/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">54</figureCitation>
). Palptibia with two divergent petal-like projections: antiaxial projection longer, widened medially, rounded distally, with small subapical incision, and small lamellar prominence at its inner base; paraxial projection shorter, subtriangular, and tapered toward obtuse apex (
<figureCitation box="[989,1076,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Figs 21</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1088,1120,763,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="11.[151,263,874,897]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,853]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,853]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39. Palptibial projections, males. 36. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) abludens sp. nov.; 37. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov.; 38. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) marcovallei sp. nov.; 39. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) pantinii sp. nov. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322035/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="101" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,2011]" box="[199,475,798,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,475,798,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,468,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">FEMALE</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis box="[199,390,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Dorsal idiosoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[409,495,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 15" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1835,1858]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,743,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,735,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 15. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov., female. 14. Dorsal idiosoma; 15. Ventral idiosoma. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322030/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Dorsal shield 780–925 µm long and 460–560 µm wide, elongated and suboval (length/width 1.63–1.85), delicately and evenly reticulated on surface, bearing 30 pairs of dorsal setae. Dorsal setae uniform, smooth and needle-shaped, mostly subequal in length, relatively longer and mostly with tips reaching to or beyond insertions of following setae; setae z1 shortest. For length and spacing of some selected dorsal shield setae see 
<tableCitation box="[257,340,978,1003]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="12.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1374,202,1650]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in µm) of four species of Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF0B667F2E0AC460A69EFF4CFBEF60F6" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" tableUuid="DF0B667F2E0AC460A69EFF4CFBEF60F6">Table 1</tableCitation>
. Dorsolateral soft integument with seven pairs of marginal setae (r6, R1, R3‒R7).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis box="[199,389,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Ventral idiosoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[404,486,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 15" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1835,1858]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,743,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,735,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 15. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov., female. 14. Dorsal idiosoma; 15. Ventral idiosoma. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322030/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Sternal shield 270–290 µm long, slightly shorter than genitiventral shield (length of sternal shield/length of genitiventral shield 0.9–0.95). Genitiventral shield almost subequal in length and width (length 289–318 µm, width 289–310 µm, length/width 0.93–1.05). Anal shield subtriangular, 121–143 µm long and 173–213 µm wide (length/width 0.58–0.74); anus with three circum-anal setae situated close to posterior margin of shield. Peritremes normally developed, anterior tips reaching dorsal surface close to insertions of setae z1. Ventral shields with delicate reticulation on surface. Metapodal platelets minuscule, free on soft integument. Ventral soft integument with nine pairs of ventral setae (JV2–JV5, ZV1–ZV5). Ventral setae similar to those on dorsal idiosoma.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis box="[199,504,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Sperm induction structures</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[520,608,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Figs 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[621,696,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 26" captionStartId="8.[151,263,977,1000]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,957]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,957]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 26. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov., sperm induction structures, female, variant forms. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322032/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">23‒26</figureCitation>
). Tubiform structures of sperm induction system well developed, relatively large, with apices adjacent but separated, weakly sclerotised except short apical to subapical portions, moderately and regularly narrowed toward apices, with bases closely abutting anterior inner margin of coxae IV.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis box="[199,470,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Gnathosomal structures</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[487,621,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Figs 17, 18</figureCitation>
). Corniculi elongated and horn-like; laciniae densely pilose, as long as corniculi; deutosternum with six rows of denticles; subcapitular setae smooth and needle-shaped. Epistome with subtriangular and regularly narrowed base, narrow central neck and widened apical part densely crenulate anteriorly; basal part with denticulate lateral margins (
<figureCitation box="[770,855,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Fixed digit of chelicera with bifid terminal hook, one large distal tooth associated with pilus dentilis, and one additional distal denticle on lateral ridge; pilus dentilis well developed, curved and directed backward; movable digit of chelicera unidentate, with simple hook and one distal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[291,375,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis box="[199,252,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Legs</emphasis>
. Leg setation normal for genus (Mašán, 2007). Tarsus II with two spur-like distal setae, pl1 and pl2 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,224,1735,1758]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[224,268,1738,1757]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">MALE</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[267,274,1734,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[286,479,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Dorsal idiosoma</emphasis>
. Dorsal shield 720‒810 µm long and 425‒475 µm wide, elongated and suboval (length/width 1.62‒1.71).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis box="[199,395,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Ventral idiosoma</emphasis>
. Sternal, genitiventral, peritrematal, metapodal and anal plates fused to form an entire holoventral shield bearing nine pairs of setae (st1‒st5, JV1‒JV3, ZV2), not including three circum-anal setae close to anus; shield with reticulate sculpture on surface. Dorsolateral and ventral soft integument with 13 pairs of setae (r6, R1, R3‒R7, JV4, JV5, Zv1, ZV3‒ZV5). Dorsal and ventral chaetotaxy and other characters as in female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,2011]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,680]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="101" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis box="[199,468,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Gnathosomal structures</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[484,615,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">Figs 20, 21</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[628,658,1951,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="11.[151,263,874,897]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,853]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,853]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39. Palptibial projections, males. 36. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) abludens sp. nov.; 37. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov.; 38. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) marcovallei sp. nov.; 39. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) pantinii sp. nov. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322035/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">37</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[670,702,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 56" captionStartId="19.[151,263,1900,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,195,1879]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 56. Chelicerae, males, with variant forms of spermatodactyls. 53. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) abludens sp. nov.; 54. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov.; 55. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) pantinii sp. nov.; 56. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) marcovallei sp. nov. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322039/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="100">54</figureCitation>
). Cheliceral spermatodactyl 130‒150 µm in length, 2‒2.25 times as long as movable digit, expanded submedially, slightly curved, leaf-like to scimitar-like, with smooth margins and relatively wide terminal portion (
<figureCitation box="[586,677,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">Figs 20</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[692,724,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 56" captionStartId="19.[151,263,1900,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,195,1879]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 56. Chelicerae, males, with variant forms of spermatodactyls. 53. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) abludens sp. nov.; 54. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov.; 55. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) pantinii sp. nov.; 56. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) marcovallei sp. nov. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322039/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">54</figureCitation>
). Palptibiae slightly thickened basally, each bearing a pair of petal-like projections on proximal ventral surface, as in 
<figureCitation box="[778,862,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">Figs 21</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[917,948,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="11.[151,263,874,897]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,853]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,853]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39. Palptibial projections, males. 36. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) abludens sp. nov.; 37. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov.; 38. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) marcovallei sp. nov.; 39. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) pantinii sp. nov. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322035/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">37</figureCitation>
; projections relatively large, with divergent adjacent margins: antiaxial projection longer, with narrow base, wide medial expansion, rounded distal margin, small subapical incision and small lamellar prominence at its inner base; paraxial projection shorter, subtriangular, widened basally and tapered toward obtuse apex. Palpfemur with distinct papular tubercle on anterolateral basal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis box="[199,252,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">Legs</emphasis>
. Medial segments of legs II spurred on their distal ventral surface: femur with one robust spur, genu and tibia each with a peg-like spur, as in 
<figureCitation box="[557,639,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
. Femoral spur broadened in basal part, produced into narrowly rounded apex, with two small tubercles on axillary side (
<figureCitation box="[700,786,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,201,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1814]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) bergomensis sp. nov. 16. Sperm induction structures, female; 17. Epistome, female; 18. Chelicera, female; 19. Tarsus II, female, mediodistal part; 20. Chelicera, male; 21. Palptibial projections, male; 22. Ventral spurs on leg II (femur, genu and tibia), male. Not scaled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322031/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Terminal part of tarsus II with only one spur-like distal seta, pl1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="101" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,511,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">Etymology.</emphasis>
The epithet of this species is derived from the Latin name “ 
<emphasis box="[1010,1132,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">Bergomum</emphasis>
” (Bergamo) and alludes to the 
<typeStatus box="[192,240,549,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">type</typeStatus>
locality situated in the urban area of Bergamo City.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,406,583,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="101">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
The new species may be distinguished from the other congeners by the characters discussed in the diagnosis (see above), and the key below. In addition, the species differs from the related species by the features listed in 
<tableCitation box="[343,429,655,680]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="16.[146,221,530,550]" captionText="TABLE 2. Comparative characteristics of selected features in the Pachylaelaps (Longipachylaelaps) species. SL = length of cheliceral spermatodactyl, MDL = length of movable digit of chelicera, ― = unknown adult stage,? = unknown character)." pageId="6" pageNumber="101">Table 2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
